ç        | This  document describes VMARC version 1.2.15 and all subse-
ç          quent versions until superceded.   Version 1.2 of  VMARC  is
ç          substantially  a  total reorganization of previous versions.
ç          In addition, the following changes in  function  are  intro-
ç          duced.
 
          LIST  function added:  The members of an archive can be dis-
          LIST  function added:
          LIST  function added:
ç          LIST  function added:
ç          played by using the LIST function of  VMARC.    Uncompacting
ç          the archive to list the members is no longer required.
 
          LOAD, DUMP, TLOAD, and TDUMP superceded:  The device support
          LOAD, DUMP, TLOAD, and TDUMP superceded:
          LOAD, DUMP, TLOAD, and TDUMP superceded:
ç          LOAD, DUMP, TLOAD, and TDUMP superceded:
ç          for tapes and the virtual reader, punch and printer has been
ç          incorporated  into the PACK, UNPACK and LIST functions.  In-
ç          put or output devices  are  specified  in  the  command-line
ç          options  rather  than  by distinct functions.  The functions
ç          LOAD, DUMP, TLOAD, and TDUMP are still accepted by VMARC for
ç          compatibility with previous releases, but may  be  withdrawn
ç          in future releases.
 
