ç          where
 
ç          infileid       specifies  the input file(s) to be processed.
ç                         Asterisks and percent-signs may  be  included
ç                         in the input file identifier as wildcard sym-
ç                         bols  to  specify  groups of CMS files.  This
ç                         parameter is required.
 
ç          outfileid      specifies the output  file(s).    Equal-signs
ç                         may   be  used  in  place  of  the  filename,
ç                         filetype, or filemode to indicate  that  that
ç                         part of the file identifier should be derived
ç                         from the input file identifier.  This parame-
ç                         ter,  therefore, may specify a single file to
ç                         hold all of the compacted input files, or  it
ç                         may  specify potentially a different file for
ç                         each.  This operand may not be used if output
ç                         is to a device (tape, punch or printer).   If
ç                         output is to disk and the outfileid parameter
ç                         is omitted, output file(s) replace the input.
