          Usage Notes.
          Usage Notes.
          Usage Notes.
ç          Usage Notes.
 
ç          1.  When  appending to an existing archive, any value speci-
ç              fied with the BLOCK  option  is  ignored.    The  record
ç              length of the existing archive is used instead.
è 
ç          VMARC                                                      7
ª 
                               VMARC Version 1.2
                               VMARC Version 1.2
                               VMARC Version 1.2
ç                               VMARC Version 1.2
 
ç          2.  Separate  archives (with identical BLOCK specifications)
ç              can be combined into a single archive by simple  concat-
ç              enation.    For  example, ARC2 VMARC A could be added to
ç              the end of ARC1 VMARC A by the COPYFILE command:
 
ç                COPYFILE  ARC2 VMARC A  ARC1 VMARC A  ( APPEND
 
ç          3.  Since  the output file name and type may be derived from
ç              the corresponding parts of the input file names,  it  is
ç              possible  for  multiple input files (specified by a pat-
ç              tern) to map into the same output file.  For example,
 
ç                VMARC  PACK  * * A  = VMARC A
 
ç              could map the files TEST EXEC and TEST FORTRAN  both  to
ç              the output file TEST VMARC.  When this type of situation
ç              occurs  VMARC  handles  it  in what would seem to be the
ç              most natural fashion.   The first time  a  given  output
ç              file is used VMARC obeys the APPEND or REPLACE option if
ç              specified.    For  the second and all subsequent uses of
ç              the output file, VMARC unconditionally appends.
 
ç          4.  Similar to the behavior of the TAPE command,  after  the
ç              last  archive  member is written to tape, VMARC writes a
ç              tape mark then backspaces over the tape mark.  The  tape
ç              file  has  end-of-file  properly marked, and the tape is
ç              positioned such that a second use of VMARC can append to
ç              the tape file.  If the user wishes  to  create  separate
ç              tape  files, it is recommended that the TAPE WTM command
ç              be used between applications of VMARC.  That is,
 
ç                VMARC PACK ... ( TAP1
ç                TAPE WTM 1
ç                VMARC PACK ... ( TAP1
 
ç              Whether one or many files are written, it is also recom-
ç              mended that two tape marks be  written  after  the  last
ç              file.
