ç          infileid  specifies the CMS file identifier  for  the  input
ç                    archives.   Asterisks and percents may be included
ç                    in the filename,  and  filetype  as  wildcards  to
ç                    specify  groups of CMS files.  The asterisk may be
ç                    used in place of the file mode to specify all  ac-
ç                    cessed  disks.   This operand is required when the
ç                    input is from disk, and it is disallowed when  in-
ç                    put is from a device.
 
ç          pattern   specifies  the  filename  and  filetype of members
ç                    that should be extracted.  Asterisks and  percent-
ç                    signs  may  be  used  as pattern-matching symbols.
ç                    The pattern parameter also specifies the  filemode
ç                    for the disk where the extracted members should be
ç                    written.    If  omitted,  VMARC uses * * A for the
ç                    pattern.
 
