          Notes.
          Notes.
          Notes.
ç          Notes.
 
ç          1.  When input is taken from the virtual  card  reader,  the
ç              disposition  of the reader file when VMARC has completed
ç              processing depends  on  several  factors.    The  normal
ç              action  for  VMARC  is  to purge the file from the spool
ç              queue.  If the input is only partially processed, either
ç              because  of  an  error  or because of a member selection
ç              pattern that excludes one or more archive  members,  the
ç              file  is  retained for possible reprocessing.  There are
ç              two ways that you can  force  VMARC  to  not  purge  the
ç              reader  file, even if it is processed completely without
ç              error.  You can change the characteristics of your  vir-
ç              tual  reader  to  HOLD with the CP SPOOL command, or you
ç              can specify the HOLD option to VMARC.  Either way, VMARC
ç              will not purge the reader file at completion.
