          Options unique to the PACK function.
          Options unique to the PACK function.
          Options unique to the PACK function.
ç          Options unique to the PACK function.
 
ç          S2             The  S2 data compaction method is used.  This
ç                         method usually produces smaller results  than
ç                         the   LZW   method,   but  it  requires  more
ç                         processor time to produce.    (During  uncom-
ç                         paction, the S2 and LZW methods have compara-
ç                         ble execution speed.)
 
ç          LZW            The LZW data compaction method is used.  This
ç                         method  is  used by default if neither S2 nor
ç                         STORE are specified.
 
ç          STOre          Data compaction is not be used.  This  option
ç                         should  be used for those few cases where the
ç                         LZW and S2 methods fail to produce  a  result
ç                         significantly smaller than the original.  The
ç                         result  produced  with  the STORE option will
ç                         always be slightly larger than  the  original
ç                         because  of  the  overhead  needed  to record
ç                         structural information.
 
ç          APPend         Allows output be appended to an existing  ar-
ç                         chive.    If the output file does not already
ç                         exist, it is created.  If it does  exist,  it
ç                         should  be an archive created by VMARC.  How-
ç                         ever, VMARC does not verify that  the  output
ç                         is a well-formed archive.  The only test per-
ç                         formed  is  that  the output file must have a
ç                         fixed-length record structure.
 
ç          NOAPPend       Restricts output from being  appended  to  an
ç                         existing archive.  This is the default.
 
          BLock nnnn     Requests  that  nnnn  be  used for the record
ç                                         ____
ç                         length of output file.  For disk  files,  the
ç                         default is 80; for tape, it is 4096.  The op-
ç                         tion is not allowed for punch or printer out-
ç                         put.
 
ç          PRinter        Requests  that output be directed to the vir-
ç                         tual line printer rather than to disk.
 
ç          PRt            This is a synonym for PRINT.
 
ç          PUNch          Requests that output be directed to the  vir-
ç                         tual card punch rather than to disk.
