          Error messages
          Error messages
          Error messages
          Error messages
ç          ______________
 
ç          Æ   nnnnnnnn   tttttttt   mm.   Bytes   in=xxxxxxxx,   bytes
ç              out=yyyyyyyy (zzzzzz%)
 
ç              After each archive member is processed VMARC generates a
ç              trace message.  The message reports  the  member's  ori-
ç              ginal fileid and the number of bytes read, the number of
ç              bytes  written,  and  the ratio of the two.  The message
ç              can be suppressed with the NOTRACE option on the command
ç              line.  When packing, the ratio displayed in the  message
ç              is  the  compaction  factor; the smaller the number, the
ç              higher the degree of compaction achieved.  When  unpack-
ç              ing,  the  ratio  is the expansion factor.  When listing
ç              the membership of an archive, the number of bytes  writ-
ç              ten and the ratio display as zero.
 
ç          Æ   Cannot append to input file.
 
ç              The  output  file is the same as the input file, and AP-
ç              PEND was specified.  Correct the output  or  input  file
ç              name parameter, then retry the command.
 
ç          Æ   Extraneous parameters on command line.
 
ç              You entered more parameters on the command line then the
ç              VMARC  program expected.   For example, you may have in-
ç              cluded an input fileid when unpacking from  the  virtual
ç              reader.   Eliminate the extra parameters, then retry the
ç              command.
 
ç          Æ   File VMARC MODULE mm will not be processed.
 
ç              The input file name or pattern specified for  an  opera-
ç              tion  matched  the name of the VMARC program.  There re-
ç              ally is no point to compacting the VMARC  program  since
ç              the  original  is needed to extract it.  The program ig-
ç              nores any such request.  If you really, really  do  want
ç              to archive the VMARC program, copy the VMARC MODULE file
ç              to  a  file  named VMARCX MODULE.  Use VMARCX to compact
ç              the VMARC MODULE.
 
ç          Æ   Incomplete input file specification.
 
ç              Either the CMS file name, file type  or  file  mode  was
ç              omitted for the input file.  You must specify the output
ç              file's complete fileid.
 
ç          Æ   Incomplete output file specification.
 
ç              Either  the  CMS  file  name, file type or file mode was
ç              omitted for the output file.  You must specify the  out-
ç              put file's complete fileid.
 
ç          VMARC                                                     16
ª 
                               VMARC Version 1.2
                               VMARC Version 1.2
                               VMARC Version 1.2
ç                               VMARC Version 1.2
 
ç          Æ   Input file not found.
 
ç              The  file  specified  for input could not be located, or
ç              the pattern specified for input did not match any files.
ç              Verify that the input file or pattern  is  entered  cor-
ç              rectly.  Retry the command.
 
ç          Æ   Input fileid is invalid.
 
ç              The  file  name, type or mode entered for the input file
ç              contains invalid characters.  Verify that the input file
ç              name or pattern is entered correctly.   Retry  the  com-
ç              mand.
 
ç          Æ   Invalid header for compacted file.
 
ç              An  UNPACK or LIST function was requested on a file that
ç              does not appear to be a file originally created by  this
ç              utility.  Verify that the input file is correctly speci-
ç              fied, and retry the command.
 
ç          Æ   Invalid numeric value xxxxxxxx
 
ç              VMARC  was  expecting to find a valid number immediately
ç              following a command line option such as BLOCK.  What was
ç              found is either out of range  for  the  option  (e.g.  a
ç              block  size  larger  than 32767) or not a number at all.
ç              Correct the command line, then retry the command.
 
ç          Æ   Invalid or conflicting option xxxxxxxx
 
ç              An option specified on the command line for VMARC (after
ç              the open parenthesis) is  either  not  allowed  for  the
ç              function  that  was requested (e.g., STORE with the LIST
ç              option) or in conflict with another option that  appears
ç              eariler  on  the command line (e.g. APPEND after REPLACE
ç              has  already  been  specified).    Correct  the  command
ç              options, then retry the command.
 
ç          Æ   Missing numeric value for xxxxxxxx
 
ç              VMARC  was  expecting to find a valid number immediately
ç              following a command line option such as BLOCK,  but  the
ç              option  was  at  the end of the command line (so nothing
ç              follows it).  Correct the command line, then  retry  the
ç              command.
 
ç          Æ   New version of VMARC required for this file.
 
ç              An UNPACK function was requested on a file that was cre-
ç              ated  by  a  later  version  of the VMARC program.   You
ç              should obtain the latest version of VMARC to process the
ç              file.
