          Installation and Maintenance
          Installation and Maintenance
          Installation and Maintenance
          Installation and Maintenance
ç          ____________________________
 
ç          The  VMARC  utility  program  is available from a variety of
ç          sources, with the principal  distribution  point  being  the
ç          LISTSERV  server located on the Bitnet node RPIECS.  New re-
ç          leases and fixes are always posted to LISTSERV  first.    If
ç          you  have  access  to Bitnet you may obtain the most current
ç          version of VMARC by issuing the following CMS command.
 
ç            TELL LISTSERV AT RPIECS GET VMARC PACKAGE
 
ç        | The RPIECS site has VMARC up to level 1.2.20.  As of 14  Oc-
ç        | tober   1998,   VMARC   is  now  available  on  the  web  at
ç        | <http://www.geocities.com/SiliconValley/Garage/3246/>,  with
ç        | all updates including those before and after level 1.2.21.
 
ç          You eventually should receive three files in Netdata format.
 
ç          VMARC MODULE      the  executable module for the VMARC util-
ç                            ity.
 
ç          VMARC VMARC       an archive of the program source and  doc-
ç        |                   umentation including all current updates.
 
ç          VMARC $PACKAGE    a  "packing  list"  of what is included in
ç        |                   the VMARC PACKAGE (not  in  the  web  site
ç        |                   files).
 
ç          There  may be additional files included in the package.  Be-
ç          fore proceeding further, examine the VMARC $PACKAGE file for
ç          a a complete inventory of what is included  in  the  package
ç          and  any  special  instructions  or notes about handling the
ç          package.
 
ç          If you are interested only in the (executable)  program  and
ç          its  documentation,  you  can extract just the documentation
ç          from the archive using the command
 
ç            VMARC UNPACK VMARC VMARC A * SCRIPT A (REPLACE
 
ç          For the complete VMARC package,  including  program  source,
ç          you should extract all members of the archive using the com-
ç          mand
 
ç            VMARC UNPACK VMARC VMARC A * * A (REPLACE
 
ç          The  VMARC program is written in IBM/370 assembler language.
ç          Complete source is provided  in  the  distribution  package.
ç          The  update facilities of CMS are exploited to manage source
ç          changes, so in addition to the base assembler source,  there
ç          are  control  and update files as well.  To rebuild the exe-
ç        | cutable module from source, use the following commands, add-
è 
ç          VMARC                                                     20
ª 
                               VMARC Version 1.2
                               VMARC Version 1.2
                               VMARC Version 1.2
ç                               VMARC Version 1.2
 
ç        | ing "( SYSPARM CMSn" to the VMFASM command if  you  need  to
ç        | force assembly for a specific CMS level.
 
ç            VMFASM VMARC VMARC
ç        |   LOAD   VMARC (ORIGIN 20000
ç            GENMOD VMARC
 
ç          The  VMFASM  command is provided with CMS to support mainte-
ç          nance of the operating system.  If it is unavailable to you,
ç          contact your local systems programmer for assistance.
 
          If you need to modify the VMARC program, please, do not mod-
ç                                                           ___________
          ify the source directly  Instead, use the update  management
ç          _______________________
ç          facilities of XEDIT:
 
ç            XEDIT VMARC ASSEMBLE A ( CTL VMARC
 
ç          If  the  above  command is used, XEDIT will keep all of your
ç          changes in a separate "update" file  named  VMARC  UPDTLOCL.
ç          The  commands  given earlier to rebuild the module can still
ç          be used, and the new module will include your changes.
